<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="491" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,258,1075]" pageId="5" pageNumber="491">Pale ochraceous with green tinge, especially on tibiae and tarsi, (in life uniformly green). Abdominal sterna yellow. Muscle impressions on frontoclypeus sometimes pale brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,258,1075]" pageId="5" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis box="[199,368,331,355]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="491">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer dorsal margin sinuate, posterodorsally rounded, ventral margin concave medially, ventral process distally narrowed and pointed, exceeding dorsal margin of pygofer. Subgenital plate longer than broad, with numerous marginal long hair-like setae in distal half and two stout short macrosetae. Style S-shaped, without preapical lobe, posterior apex rounded with numerous rugae forming toothlike projections in lateral view. Connective Y-shaped, stem shorter than arms. Arms of ventral process of aedeagus running together, slightly curved dorsally in lateral view, each arm slightly narrowed near apex with crenulated margin and bluntly pointed; aedeagus membranous, shaft tubular in distal half, apex bifid, atrium well developed, gonopore apical. Segment X large, its ventral margin produced anteriorly into process with serrated margin. Anal style slightly longer than broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,258,1075]" pageId="5" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis box="[199,393,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="491">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Seventh sternite longer than wide, medially ridged, gradually narrowed posteriorly with posterior margin concave with rounded lateral margins. First and second pair of valvulae as in 
<figureCitation box="[1210,1340,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 90" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1873,1896]" captionTargetBox="[204,1390,208,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[191,1396,193,1853]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 90. Female ovipositor in species of Signoretia. 80 – 83. S. sahyadrica sp. nov. 80. First pair of valvula; 81. First pair of valvula apex; 82. Second pair of valvula; 83. Apex of second pair of valvula. 84 – 86. S. lunglei sp. nov. 84. Ovipositor, lateral view; 85. Apex of first pair of valvula; 86. Apex of second pair of valvula. 87 – 90. S. maculata Baker; 87. First pair of valvula; 88. Apex of first pair of valvula; 89. Second pair of valvula; 90. Apex of second pair of valvula." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167197/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="491">Figs 84–86</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
