<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="491" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,258,1075]" pageId="5" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,978,1003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="491">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species does not have any dark markings on the body. Both 
<taxonomicName box="[1091,1200,979,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lunglei">
<emphasis box="[1091,1200,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="491">S. lunglei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1260,1373,979,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takiyae">
<emphasis box="[1260,1373,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="491">S. takiyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have similar male genitalia, however, 
<taxonomicName box="[517,627,1014,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takiyae">
<emphasis box="[517,627,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="491">S. takiyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dark markings on the crown and has the arms of the ventral process of the aedeagus divergent right from the base.
</paragraph>
